1. Kubernetes Overview

Kubernetes is a production-grade, open-source platform designed to automate the deployment, scaling, and management of containerized applications. 

It acts as the "Operating System" for your cloud-native infrastructure, abstracting away the underlying hardware to focus on application delivery.

The project was open-sourced by Google in 2014, based on over 15 years of experience running production workloads at scale (using an internal system called Borg).

It is now governed by the Cloud Native Computing Foundation (CNCF).
